'''''Purple Saturn Day''''' is a space-themed [[Olympic games|Olympic]] [[sports game]]. It was created by [[ERE Informatique]] and published by [[Epyx]] in 1989.

==Gameplay==
The game features four non-existent [[science fiction|sci-fi]] themed Olympic games, in the vein of Epyx games like ''[[Summer Games (video game)|Summer Games]]'' (1984). The four events are Ring Chase, Tronic Slider, Brain Bowler, and Time Jump.<ref>https://amr.abime.net/review_48054</ref> The events can be practiced on their own, or played one after another in tournament mode, where if the player wins they get to see the queen of the tournament do a short dance around a pole.

